HEADWORD: Senescent
<hw>Se*nes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>senescent</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>senescere</ets> to grow old, incho.
fr. <ets>senere</ets> to be old.]</ety> <def>Growing old; decaying with
the lapse of time.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The night was
<xex>senescent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Poe.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧With too
<xex>senescent</xex> air.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seneschal</ent>⟦br⟧
